The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Monday, October 14, 2002 				 Radcliffe smashes world mark
				 	 Paula Radcliffe after winning the Chicago Marathon on Sunday																								Chicago: Britains Paula Radcliffe won the womens race at the Chicago Marathon on Sunday in a world record time of 2::17:18 seconds.																								Radcliffe destroyed by nearly a minute and a half the old record set at 2::18:47 by Catherine Ndereba of Kenya in last years race. Ndereba had to settle for second best this time, trailing in at 2::19:25.																								There had been hopes of a world record in the mens race as well but Khalid Khannouchis 2::05:56 was 18 seconds outside the mark set by the Moroccan-born American at the London Marathon in April.																								Daniel Njenga of Kenya and Toshinari Takaoka of Japan finished second in the same time on 2::06:16 with Paul Tergat of Kenya two seconds behind them.																								Radcliffe, who won the London Marathon, said: I was really surprised how much support there was for me. There were so many British flags. (REUTERS)
